<br>
Sorry Snyde, you are a bit off center.<br>
<br>
Pot grown now compared to pot grown in the 60's is WAY more potent.  If you had a beer with only 2% alcohol and one with 4.5%, would you say one is more potent than the other?<br>
<br>
Just like there are different varieties of flowers, there are different varieties of Marijuana.<br>
<br>
For instance, the pot used to make hemp rope has been manipulated thru breeding to produce a heavier, thicker, more fiberous stalk.  THis is what they use to make the rope.  They didn't want pot plants that bud with big buds because it takes away from the size of the overall plant.<br>
<br>
Growers have been cross-breeding plants like this for thousands of years.<br>
<br>
I know, you're gonna say I don't know shit.<br>
<br>
To create a cross bread plant, all you need to a shoot from one breed of plant and the growing plant of  another.  make a small incision in one of the main stems that shoot out from the &quot;trunk&quot;, take the graft from the other plant, cut the very end off in the form of a point, and stick it in the groove you cut from the first plant.  THey make a special chemical that helps the plant &quot;heal&quot; and also make a special &quot;band-aid&quot; for it.<br>
<br>
The new shoot will produce a bud that is a cross between the two plants.<br>
<br>
You can also take a plant that is a female, cover one of the buds with a baggie and shake some pollen out.  Then take that bag to another plant and cover a bud and shake it.  When that bud grows seeds, the seed will be a combination of the two varieties.  Cross Pollenating.<br>
<br>
People do it with roses, and so many other plants.<br>
<br>
What has happened since the 60's is that growers have taken shoots from varieties that naturally yield large blooms, and cross is with strains that have a high THC count.  Breed the plant thru a couple of generations and bam, you have a strain of marijuana with a THC count higher than the two original plants.<br>
<br>
Essentially growing more potent (higher THC count) marijuana.<br>
<br>
I smoke pot like a champ, not bragging or anything, just establishing a point.  I can smoke a joint the size of a kielbasa in a small BMW, with the windows rolled up until I can't see out the windows.  But if I am in a room with a smoker, I start gasping for breath.<br>
<br>
Pot isn't nearly as much of an issue as cigarettes made by the good folks like Phillip-Morris. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.maine.rr.com/waassaap/newtag.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/bdrinal28133.showUserPublicProfile?gid=torunkes>Torunkes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>S&M Barbie</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/22/02 8:53:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm37.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=86>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This just in</span><hr size=1> well, pot was actually legal before the &quot;american government&quot; was around, and it's legal in a large amount of european countries such as germany and amsterdam<br>
